    "name": {
      "zh": "西蒙诺夫 AG-043 5.45x39突击步枪",
      "en": "Simonov AG-043 5.45x39 assault rifle"
    },
    "shortName": {
      "zh": "AG-043",
      "en": "AG-043"
    },
    "description": {
      "zh": "AG-043是一款苏联研制的紧凑型全自动突击步枪，使用5.45x39毫米弹药，由谢尔盖·西蒙诺夫于1974年开发。该步枪的设计源于GRAU发起的“现代项目”。在这场苏联设计竞赛中，最终胜出的是卡拉什尼科夫设计的AKS-74U。",
      "en": "The AG-043 was a Soviet compact fully automatic assault rifle chambered for the 5.45x39mm round, developed in 1974 by Sergei Simonov. The rifle was designed after the GRAU launched Project Modern. The Soviet contest for this design was eventually won out by Kalashnikov's AKS-74U."
    },
